 {\bf e_n^T x } 
 {\bf e_n^T} = (0, 0 \cdots 0 , 1, 0 \cdots 0 , 0)
{\bf x^T A x} = 1
{\bf A}
\nabla({\bf e_n^T x} + \lambda \; {\bf x^T A x})=0 
 {\bf e_n } + 2 \lambda \; {\bf A x} = {\bf 0} \Rightarrow {\bf x = }\alpha \; {\bf A^{-1} e_n}
{\bf x^T A x} = 1
\alpha^2 = \frac{1}{\bf e_n^TA^{-1} e_n}
 {\bf x} = \pm  \frac{{\bf A^{-1} e_n}}{\sqrt{\bf e_n^TA^{-1} e_n}}
